# proxies.txt — one proxy per line. Rename to proxies.txt to activate.
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Accepted formats (HTTP/HTTPS only — aiohttp does not support SOCKS natively):
#   host:port
#   user:pass@host:port
#   http://host:port
#   http://user:pass@host:port
#   https://user:pass@host:port
#
# Examples (fake — replace with real proxies):
# 192.0.2.10:8080
# user:pass@192.0.2.11:8080
# http://192.0.2.12:3128
# http://user:pass@proxy.example.com:8080
#
# Tips:
#   - Residential or ISP proxies work best (fewer Mojang bans)
#   - Datacenter proxies get rate-limited faster but are cheap
#   - ~50-100 proxies is enough for a continuous 3-char scan
#   - ~500+ for aggressive 4-char scanning (37^4 = 1.87M names)
